The paper deals with the problem of joint subcarrier and power allocation in a multi-user OFDMA system, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which falls under the category of algorithms and complexity (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes different utility functions to optimize the allocation, which can be considered as a machine learning approach (cs.LG). Finally, the paper assumes perfect channel knowledge, which is a common assumption in signal processing (cs.SI).
